    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM AXLE: INTERNATIONAL - LUBRICATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>LUBRICATION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>To ensure proper lubrication and operating temperature, correct lubricants and lubricant levels must
                be maintained.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Lubricant close enough to bottom of opening to be seen or touched is not sufficient. Lubricant
                        must be level with opening (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1400957">Figure 57</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1400957" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400957" filename="../figg14/g1400957.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Lubricant Level With Opening</caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="t1400905">
                <title>Lubricant Capacities</title>
                <tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="3.10in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="3" spanname="1to3"/>
                    <thead valign="bottom">
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="bottom">
                                <para>CAPACITY (Approximate)*</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="bottom">
                                <para>PTS.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="bottom">
                                <para>LITERS</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Forward Rear Axle**</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>32.5</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>15.6</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Rear Rear Axle</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>44.6</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>21.3</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="1to3" align="center">
                                <para>* Capacity will vary depending on the housing angle in each vehicle. Fill to the
                                    lower edge of fill hole in rear of axle housing, as shown above.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="1to3" align="center">
                                <para>** Pour 1 pint (0.5 liter) of gear lube into the filler hole in top of inter-axle
                                    differential cover. Replace fill plug and torque to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <table id="t1400906">
                <title>Maximum Oil Sump Temperature Table</title>
